    "body": "## Problem\r\nDiagnostics are only pulled for the current buffer. If you have two open files with diagnostics and fix an issue in file A that should result in no diagnostics in file B, the diagnostics in file B will remain until you open file B.\r\n\r\nAnother thing to note is that in some LSPs (or at least the one I’m using), calling workspace diagnostics does not return diagnostics for open files.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nOn file changes, call diagnostics for all open files.\r\nIs that okay?",
    "closed_at": null,
